TY  - JOUR
T1  - Exposing Pay Secrecy
AU  - Colella, Adrienne
AU  - Paetzold, Ramona L.
AU  - Zardkoohi, Asghar
AU  - Wesson, Michael J.
Y1  - 2007/01/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.23463701
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2007.23463701
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 55
EP  - 71
VL  - 32
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Pay secrecy is a contentious issue in many organizations and a controversial one in our society. However, there has been little scholarly research on this topic. We hope to address this void by exposing the complexity of pay secrecy as a construct. What are its costs and benefits? What factors affect the link between pay secrecy and the extent to which it is a cost or benefit? This article reveals the complexity of pay secrecy and, we hope, generates ideas for much new research in the broad management field.
AB  - Pay secrecy is a contentious issue in many organizations and a controversial one in our society. However, there has been little scholarly research on this topic. We hope to address this void by exposing the complexity of pay secrecy as a construct. What are its costs and benefits? What factors affect the link between pay secrecy and the extent to which it is a cost or benefit? This article reveals the complexity of pay secrecy and, we hope, generates ideas for much new research in the broad management field.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.23463701
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2007.23463701
Y2  - 2026/04/24
