TY  - JOUR
T1  - Relational Archetypes, Organizational Learning, and Value Creation: Extending the Human Resource Architecture
AU  - Kang, Sung-Choon
AU  - Morris, Shad S.
AU  - Snell, Scott A.
Y1  - 2007/01/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.23464060
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2007.23464060
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 236
EP  - 256
VL  - 32
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Theories of knowledge-based competition emphasize the firm's ability both to explore and to exploit knowledge as the source of value creation. We attempt to bring human resource management directly into this forum by introducing a framework of relational archetypes?entrepreneurial and cooperative?that are derived from unique configurations of three dimensions (structural, affective, and cognitive) of social relations within and across firm boundaries. We identify how human resource configurations can be linked to the strategic management of these relational archetypes.
AB  - Theories of knowledge-based competition emphasize the firm's ability both to explore and to exploit knowledge as the source of value creation. We attempt to bring human resource management directly into this forum by introducing a framework of relational archetypes?entrepreneurial and cooperative?that are derived from unique configurations of three dimensions (structural, affective, and cognitive) of social relations within and across firm boundaries. We identify how human resource configurations can be linked to the strategic management of these relational archetypes.
