TY  - JOUR
T1  - Bankruptcy Law and Entrepreneurship Development: A Real Options Perspective
AU  - Lee, Seung-Hyun
AU  - Peng, Mike W.
AU  - Barney, Jay B.
Y1  - 2007/01/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.23464070
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2007.23464070
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 257
EP  - 272
VL  - 32
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We develop a real options perspective to explore how an entrepreneur-friendly bankruptcy law can encourage entrepreneurship development at the societal level. If bankrupt entrepreneurs are excessively punished for failure, they may let inherently high-risk but potentially high-return opportunities pass. We suggest that a more entrepreneur-friendly bankruptcy law, informed by a real options logic, can encourage more active and vibrant entrepreneurship development. We also discuss the implications of the role of venture capital and stigma in the effectiveness of an entrepreneur-friendly bankruptcy law.
AB  - We develop a real options perspective to explore how an entrepreneur-friendly bankruptcy law can encourage entrepreneurship development at the societal level. If bankrupt entrepreneurs are excessively punished for failure, they may let inherently high-risk but potentially high-return opportunities pass. We suggest that a more entrepreneur-friendly bankruptcy law, informed by a real options logic, can encourage more active and vibrant entrepreneurship development. We also discuss the implications of the role of venture capital and stigma in the effectiveness of an entrepreneur-friendly bankruptcy law.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.23464070
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2007.23464070
Y2  - 2026/04/24
