TY  - JOUR
T1  - Managing Firm Resources in Dynamic Environments to Create Value: Looking Inside the Black Box
AU  - Sirmon, David G.
AU  - Hitt, Michael A.
AU  - Ireland, R. Duane
Y1  - 2007/01/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.23466005
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2007.23466005
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 273
EP  - 292
VL  - 32
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We address current criticisms of the RBV (oversight of dynamism, environmental contingencies, and managers' role) by linking value creation in dynamic environmental contexts to the management of firm resources. Components of the resource management model include structuring the resource portfolio; bundling resources to build capabilities; and leveraging capabilities to provide value to customers, gain a competitive advantage, and create wealth for owners. Propositions linking resource management and value creation are offered to shape future research.
AB  - We address current criticisms of the RBV (oversight of dynamism, environmental contingencies, and managers' role) by linking value creation in dynamic environmental contexts to the management of firm resources. Components of the resource management model include structuring the resource portfolio; bundling resources to build capabilities; and leveraging capabilities to provide value to customers, gain a competitive advantage, and create wealth for owners. Propositions linking resource management and value creation are offered to shape future research.
