TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Knowledge-Based View, Nested Heterogeneity, and New Value Creation: Philosophical Considerations on the Locus of Knowledge
AU  - Felin, Teppo
AU  - Hesterly, William S.
Y1  - 2007/01/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.23464020
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2007.23464020
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 195
EP  - 218
VL  - 32
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - At what level is new value created, or, put differently, what is the locus of knowledge? While knowledge and capabilities-based researchers argue that the locus of new value and knowledge lies at the firm level, we challenge this conceptualization and theoretically build toward more individualist foundations. We explicate the underlying philosophical assumptions of extant knowledge and capabilities-based work and discuss attributional problems. Nested (individual-level, a priori) heterogeneity may provide a better explanation of collective heterogeneity.
AB  - At what level is new value created, or, put differently, what is the locus of knowledge? While knowledge and capabilities-based researchers argue that the locus of new value and knowledge lies at the firm level, we challenge this conceptualization and theoretically build toward more individualist foundations. We explicate the underlying philosophical assumptions of extant knowledge and capabilities-based work and discuss attributional problems. Nested (individual-level, a priori) heterogeneity may provide a better explanation of collective heterogeneity.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.23464020
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2007.23464020
Y2  - 2026/04/24
